Html:
I would like to use progressive enhancement from my select element to rateit. But I also want to use &quot;step&quot;. Is it possible to combine the two?<br />
<br />
Basically, I want a rating from 1-10, but only want to show 5 stars. Here's what I have, but it always uses full stars.<br />
<pre><code>&lt;select id=&quot;Rating&quot; step=&quot;.5&quot;&gt;
    &lt;option value=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;/option&gt;
    &lt;option&gt;1&lt;/option&gt;
    &lt;option&gt;2&lt;/option&gt;
    &lt;option&gt;3&lt;/option&gt;
    &lt;option&gt;4&lt;/option&gt;
    &lt;option&gt;5&lt;/option&gt;
    &lt;option&gt;6&lt;/option&gt;
    &lt;option&gt;7&lt;/option&gt;
    &lt;option&gt;8&lt;/option&gt;
    &lt;option&gt;9&lt;/option&gt;
    &lt;option&gt;10&lt;/option&gt;
&lt;/select&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;rateit&quot; data-rateit-backingfld=&quot;#Rating&quot; data-rateit-step=&quot;.5&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</code></pre>

Thanks.<br />
